  "prompt": "What are the best books of body language?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended books on body language:\n\n1. \"The Definitive Book of Body Language\" by Allan and Barbara Pease\n- Comprehensive guide with detailed insights\n- Explains body language across different contexts\n\n2. \"What Every BODY is Saying\" by Joe Navarro\n- Written by a former FBI agent\n- Focuses on nonverbal communication techniques\n\n3. \"Body Language: How to Read Others' Thoughts by Their Gestures\" by Allan Pease\n- Classic book on understanding body language\n- Easy to read and practical\n\n4. \"The Power of Body Language\" by Tonya Reiman\n- Covers professional and personal communication\n- Provides strategies for reading and using body language\n\n5. \"Spy the Lie\" by Philip Houston\n- Focuses on detecting deception\n- Written by former CIA officers\n\n6. \"The Like Switch\" by Jack Schafer\n- Explains nonverbal communication and building relationships\n- Uses psychological and professional intelligence techniques\n\n7. \"Body Language: Secrets of Nonverbal Communication\" by James Borg\n- Provides practical tips for understanding body signals\n- Covers personal and professional interactions\n\nEach book offers unique perspectives on understanding and using body language effectively.",
